title: Grateful Dead Live at The Palladium on 1977-05-03
lineage: Sony ECM-33Ps>Sony TC-152 MAC > WAV > SHN
taper: Jerry Moore from first row loge or orchestra row 6 or 8
description: Promised Land, Bertha, Me & My Uncle, Peggy-O, Jack Straw, Row Jimmy, Lazy Lightning-> Supplication, Deal, Good Lovin', Ship of Fools, The Music Never Stopped Might As Well, Estimated Prophet, Sugaree, Samson & Delilah, Friend Of The Devil, Eyes Of The World-> Wharf Rat-> Not Fade Away-> Around & Around, E: Uncle John's Band

reviews.review_text:
Worth a listen for hardcore heads Sound quality issues, bass is very distorted but if you turn your bass all the way off it doesn't sound too bad. Headphone only show, when your ears get used to the sound it's enjoyable.  The energy in this show is great, Bertha rocks, Peggy-o is beautiful, Deal is sweet, Sugaree is one of the best I've heard, Eyes is great too.  Jerry sounds like May 77' Jerry and Keith is hammering away throughout.  
   I'm taking the 28th anniversary tour of May 77' so I am listening to every show note for note regardless of quality.  This show is worth a one time listen for sure, it's still May 77 :)  Sound quality knocks it down from a 5 star show to 3 star because it is a headphone only show and stuck on my computer.  Please, please somebody upload a full SBD show!!!!!
Comes A Time The second set is fantastic. The month of may has come! "Comes A Time" is stellar, mind-blowing, heart-stopping. What a solo by Jerry!

setting me on fire left the orchestra section during ship of fools and arrived in the loge for the basso profundo MNS - it's the best of the tour so far, i think, and the balcony is shakin' to its raging outro leading.  i sit to take a short break, too. 

yet another night of the first set seeming to spill over. first half of this second set is well-played, indeed, but the sugaree is the INSANE highlight, and keith and jerry are battling it out. one of the strongest estimateds of tour and i, for one, am happy for the FOTD break.  the second half belongs to jerry -  eyes is short but stellar and bridges to yet another rip-your-heart-out wharf rat, and NFA showcases some down in the weeds jamming. we're stomping and clapping and grinning our faces off, and then joint is jumping for sure as they close it down.  another fine UJB encore sends me out the door, so very deeply in love with this band and its music. is there anything better than being a deadhead?

second set is hot. this concert just blew me away.i saw them in st.louis at the arena,dekalb,northern U. and blumington,ind. state,that year,but this second set was a real treat."comes a time", what a butiful song.jerry just blew me away. great gitar work and emotional feelings.New Yorkers,you are so lucky to have seen this show.best second set in my opinion of that year.wish i was there!this is why i am a deadhead.
Primo Nice clean and present Audience recording. Great Job on this one to whomever the taper is.
